A man has tied the knot with a nurse that helped him recover after he had a ghastly motor accident. Anthony married nurse Vivian who helped him recover A Nigerina man, Anthony T-man C-J who survived a ghastly motor accident while travelling in September 2017 has married the nurse who helped save his life. Anthony who was badly injured in the accident and was admitted for months was also left with a fractured femur on the left leg and a deep gash on the right. Both looked horrifying and he had to undergo surgery five times. First, there were fears for his life. Then, it was feared that he may lose his legs. Fortunately, none of the fears materialized. Not only did Anthony recover fully, he went on to marry Vivian, a nurse who took care of him while he was admitted at the hospital. See more photos: